a is thin, use a conservative description based on the company category and careers/company page.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nExample:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"NVIDIA designs GPUs, AI accelerators, networking hardware, and software platforms used across data centers, gaming, autonomous systems, and applied machine learning.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Recruiter Standard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMinimum viable per company:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Strong signals: add 2-3 current, relevant recruiters or talent partners, then move on.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Weak signals: 1 recruiter is acceptable; for startups or thin teams, use a founder, CTO, VP Engineering, Head of Engineering, hiring manager, or technical lead.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Prefer university, campus, emerging talent, early-career, intern, new grad, SWE, AI, ML, or technical recruiting titles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- In bolster mode, technical members who are publicly hiring for their team are valid, especially for internship, new-grad, SWE, AI, ML, data, infrastructure, or product engineering roles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- US-based or clearly US-hiring people are preferred.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Never add more than 10 contacts to a company. If it already has 10 or more, skip it unless correcting stale data.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Use only public professional information. Do not scrape aggressively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRecruiter object schema:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"linkedin_url\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\